Class SSC

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nasa.gsfc.spdf.ssc.SSC

extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides a wrapper to the non-Java code of SSC (Satellite Situation Center).

      • getSatelliteLocation

        @Deprecated
protected java.lang.String[] getSatelliteLocation​(java.util.List<SatelliteSpecification> satellites,
                                                  CoordinateSystem coordSystem,
                                                  java.util.Calendar startTime,
                                                  java.util.Calendar endTime,
                                                  java.lang.String outputFormat)
                                           throws SSCException
        Deprecated.
        As of 2.0, this method exists solely to support the 1.0 public WS API implemented on top of this 2.0 implementation. It will be eliminated when this support is no longer needed.
        Requests that location information be generated for the specified satellite and time range.
        Parameters:
        satellites - the names of the satellites whose location information is being requested
        coordSystem - the coordinate system of the location information
        startTime - the start of the time range of data being requested
        endTime - the end of the time range of data being requested
        outputFormat - the format in which the requested information is to be produced. May be one of "-cdf", "-cdfUrl", "-xdf", or "-txt".
        Returns:
        array of strings containing either the local filename (when outputFormat == -cdf) or URI where the requested information is available
        Throws:
        SSCException - thrown if an error occurs

      • getSscSatId

        private java.lang.String getSscSatId​(java.lang.String spaseId)
        Gets the SSC satellite identifier associated with the given SPASE Observatory ResourceID. If the given value is not a SPASE Observatory ResourceID, the given value is returned.
        Parameters:
        spaseId - Spase/Observatory/ResourceID
        Returns:
        SSC satellite identifier associated with the given spaseId. The given value is returned if it is not a SPASE resourceID. null is returned if the given value is invalid or no SSC satellite identifier can be found.
